events.name: New York Knicks at Charlotte Hornets

headlines.description: — Gordon Hayward scored 34 points and the Charlotte Hornets beat the New York Knicks 109-88 on Monday night for their fourth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hayward scores 34 points, Hornets rout Knicks 109-88

headlines.description: — Dillon Brooks scored 21 points and the Memphis Grizzlies recovered after blowing a 16-point lead to beat the Cleveland Cavaliers 101-91 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brooks scores 21 points, Grizzlies beat Cavaliers 101-91

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo returned from a one-game absence because of a minor back injury and scored 22 points as the Milwaukee Bucks beat the Orlando Magic 121-99 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo, Bucks pull away late to beat Magic 121-99

headlines.description: — Bradley Beal scored 34 points and the Washington Wizards snapped their three-game losing streak and won at home for the first time this season, beating the Phoenix Suns 128-107 over the Phoenix Suns on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Beal scores 34, Wizards beat Suns 128-107 for first home win

headlines.description: — Trae Young scored 26 points, including the first three baskets of Atlanta's dominant start to the second half, and the Hawks beat the short-handed Philadelphia 76ers 112-94 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young's 26 points lead Hawks past short-handed 76ers, 112-94

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Dallas Mavericks
Toronto Raptors at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — CJ McCollum scored 30 points, including the go-ahead jumper with 9.6 seconds left to give the Portland Trail Blazers a 112-111 victory over the Toronto Raptors on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: McCollum's shot lifts Blazers to 112-111 win over Raptors

headlines.description: — Buddy Hield made a 3-pointer moments after Indiana’s Domantas Sabonis had a basket taken away following a replay review, and the Sacramento Kings beat the Pacers 127-122 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kings hold off Pacers 127-122 with replay help
